<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="R" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Rashness" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Rashness,</orth> 1) quickness, haste: <cit><quote>rashly, and praised be r. for it, let us know, our indiscretion sometimes serves us well,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ham 5.2.7" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. V, 2, 7</bibl></cit> (the two significations joined).<lb />2) inconsiderate haste, thoughtlessness: <bibl n="shak. tgv 3.1.30" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. III, 1, 30</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 3.2.222" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. III, 2, 222</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 3.6.127" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 III, 6, 127</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 2.1.134" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 II, 1, 134</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 3.5.53" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. III, 5, 53</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 4.3.502" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 502</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 1.1.153" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. I, 1, 153</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 2.2.124" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. II, 2, 124</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 3.11.14" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 11, 14</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>